April 1–6
	•	DATA COLLECTION PROCESS 
	⁃	Sources discovery: 
	⁃	Primary institutional sources (Transparenzportal, data.gv.at, statistik.at) identified through independent web search. 
	⁃	MA 7 Musikbeirat recommendations PDF identified via wien.gv.at. Community platforms (klingt.org, freemusicforum, phantanoise, esel.at) identified through prior knowledge of the Viennese experimental music scene. 
	⁃	Temporal scope: 
	⁃	Analysis period defined as 2022-2026. Rationale: years 2020-2021 excluded due to pandemic-related distortion of cultural activity (venue closures, event cancellations). Period 2022-2026 captures post-pandemic recovery and reconfiguration of the ecosystem. Upper limit set to 2026 to include IFG transparency data (nominative funding records available from September 2025 onward per §40k Transparenzdatenbankgesetz 2012). 
	⁃	Venue inclusion criteria:
	⁃	 Venues included if they meet at least one of the following:
	⁃	 primary or significant programming focus on experimental, improvised, electronic or contemporary music
	⁃	 documented presence of publicly funded music events 
	⁃	active role in the independent music scene regardless of formal funding status 
	⁃	⁃	Venues excluded: spaces with primary focus on visual art only, dance only, or commercial entertainment without documented connection to the field. 
	⁃	Venues marked:
	⁃	 * (secondary): present in the scene but programming focus is not primarily music or experimental work. Venues marked 
	⁃	? (uncertain): institutional or academic context that may fall outside the independent scene scope. Final decision pending further review of programming.
	⁃	Coordinate verification All venue coordinates verified manually via Google Maps and Google Plus Codes. Entries with unverified coordinates flagged in the table.
	•	social media screenshots included as valid data source for event documentation
	•	district calendars established as weekly review source during data collection phase
	•	contact with Schaltaucherin identified as potential qualitative source (pending)
